  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cumin seeds</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>allspice</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant, then transfer to a bowl to cool down – this is your <strong>Vietnamese spice blend</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch the spices like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until browned all over and beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato is softening, bash the <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Remove the tough outer layer<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and set them aside, then chop the soft inner core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> roughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 900ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.8L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sweet potato has browned and softened slightly, add the<strong> sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped lemongrass inner core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>and <strong>Vietnamese spice blend</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until the garlic has softened</p><p>Add the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong>,<strong> coconut stock</strong> and <strong>lemongrass outer layer<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cook for an initial 3-4 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p><p>Add the <strong>fine egg noodles</strong> to the pan and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles, then cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until everything's tender – this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style sweet potato cà ri noodle soup</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/vietnamese-style-sweet-potato-ca-ri-noodle-soup/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Vietnamese-style sweet potato cà ri noodle soup </strong>in bowls</p><p>Tip: Discard the outer lemongrass layer!</p><p>Tear over the<strong> coriander & mint </strong>and garnish with <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
